        {
            "_id": "5fuz5dej9owm5ap2",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
            "name": "Steal the Sun",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "reaction"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature within 30 feet of the sun-spire begins to Cast a Spell that has the fire or light trait</p><hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The sun-spire attempts to redirect the energy from the triggering effect into its sunlight stores. The sun-spire attempts to counteract the triggering spell with a [[/r {1d20+22} #counteract]]{+22} counteract bonus. If it successfully counteracts the spell, the sun-spire's sunlight stores are empowered. While empowered, the sun-spire deals an additional @Damage[2d8[fire]] damage with all of its attacks and abilities. The sun-spire remains empowered until the end of its next turn.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [
                    {
                        "domain": "damage",
                        "key": "RollOption",
                        "label": "Empowered by Steal the Sun",
                        "option": "steal-the-sun",
                        "toggleable": true
                    },
                    {
                        "damageType": "fire",
                        "diceNumber": 2,
                        "dieSize": "d8",
                        "key": "DamageDice",
                        "label": "Empowered by Steal the Sun",
                        "predicate": [
                            "steal-the-sun"
                        ],
                        "selector": "strike-damage"
                    }
                ],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "rarity": "common",
                    "value": [
                        "divine"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "aafpuxt66c9n4wag",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Beam of the Seven Suns",
            "sort": 700000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The sun-spire collects solar energy and uses the energy to create a deadly beam of fire. It fires the beam in a @Template[type:line|distance:120], dealing @Damage[11d8[fire]] damage to all creatures in the line (@Check[type:reflex|dc:33|basic:true] save). The concentrated beam ignites everything in its path, including the air, creating a wall of burning flame along the line that continues to burn until the end of the sun-spire's next turn. This wall has the effects of a 5th-rank @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Wall of Fire] spell, dealing @Damage[5d6[fire]] damage to any creature that crosses the wall or occupies the wall's area at the start of its turn. The sun-spire can't use the Beam of the Seven Suns again for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}, although rounds it's not in sunlight don't count toward this number.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
